headline: Why The RS Group LSE RS1 Story Is Shifting After Fresh Analyst Updates
summary: The latest update to the RS Group story centres on a modest shift in the fair value anchor, with the central estimate moving from £6.98 to £7.16 as analyst assumptions are refreshed. Behind that, revenue growth expectations have been reset from 3.57% to 5.02% and the discount rate has nudged from 8.57% to 8.67%, as research teams balance improving confidence in execution with a cautious eye on sector risk.
